<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>It&#39;s not like that for everyone yet, but it&#39;s pretty sweet in the sweet spot. </p> <p>The only thing I&#39;ve consistently missed is the absence of a barrier server, but it&#39;s never been a big enough part of my workflow to be worth staying on X. It may have been a rockier process than its creators envisioned in 2008 for reasons largely beyond the community&#39;s control, but I believe Wayland is destined to be forgotten in the best possible way.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/featherfurl"> /u/featherfurl </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/13ipqhq/the_best_praise_i_can_give_wayland_is_that_after/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/13ipqhq/the_best_praise_i_can_give_wayland_is_that_after/">[comments]</a></span>